\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Welcome back and congratulations on surviving Boot Camp. The theme for this week is relationships. No, you haven't strayed onto a dating site. We're not talking about the types of relationships that make adolescents embarrassed, at least not right away. We will be talking about relationships between variables. Although we didn't use the 'r' word last week, we were already talking about relationships when we started investigating how family sizes have been affected by time and location. In statistical language we'd say "we investigated the relationships between the variable's fertility, year, and geographical region." So in the last video of last week, we looked at relationships between a numeric variable and a categorical variable.\
