\cf4 This week, we cover tools for cases where both variables are categorical or both are numeric. Why do people care about relationships between variables? Most of you will have heard of risk factors for diseases. The basic idea of risk factors is that certain variables can help tell us how much more or less likely it is that a person will get a disease. Data is often used to predict events. For example, business people try to predict future sales based on seasonal and other buying patterns from the past. We investigate relationships between variables to figure out what is going on and to help us describe what is happening in the real world.\
